+
+## Apply the database migration
+
+From the solution root:
+
+```powershell
+dotnet ef database update --project src/VirtualCompany.Infrastructure --startup-project src/VirtualCompany.Api
+```
+
+## Local development authentication
+
+The API currently uses a development header-based authentication scheme behind an abstraction that can be replaced with future SSO/OIDC providers.
+
+Send these headers on authenticated requests:
+
+- `X-Auth-Subject` = required stable external subject identifier
+- `X-Auth-Email` = optional email, defaults to `<subject>@local.test`
+- `X-Auth-Name` = optional display name
+- `X-Auth-Provider` = optional provider name, defaults to `development`
+
+Example:
+
+```powershell
+curl https://localhost:7001/api/auth/me ^
+  -H "X-Auth-Subject: alice" ^
+  -H "X-Auth-Email: alice@local.test" ^
+  -H "X-Auth-Name: Alice Admin"
+```
+
+## Company context and memberships
+
+Company context is resolved per request using:
+
+- the `companyId` route value for company-scoped routes such as `/api/companies/{companyId}/...`
+- or the `X-Company-Id` header for explicit request scoping
+
+The API persists:
+
+- `users`
+- `companies`
+- `company_memberships`
+
+Membership roles supported by the current authorization policies:
+
+- `Owner`
+- `Admin`
+- `Manager`
+- `Employee`
+
+Membership status values:
+
+- `Pending`
+- `Active`
+- `Revoked`
+
+Only `Active` memberships are valid for tenant-scoped access.
+
+## Auth and tenant endpoints
+
+- `GET /api/auth/me`
+- `GET /api/auth/memberships`
+- `POST /api/auth/select-company`
+- `GET /api/companies/{companyId}/access`
+- `GET /api/companies/{companyId}/admin-access`
+- `GET /api/companies/{companyId}/memberships/{membershipId}`
+
+## Authorization behavior
+
+- Company access checks use persisted memberships resolved in the current company context.
+- Requests for a known company without an active membership return `403 Forbidden`.
+- Resource fetches that are filtered by `company_id` return `404 Not Found` when the resource is not present in the resolved tenant.
